<br>
Halo, having worked in a pscyh hospital for almost 2 years, I have come into contact with just about every psychological disease out there.  And I can tell you that some people DO commit crimes without purpose.  I dont say without reason.  The &quot;reason&quot; they do these things is because of a chemical imbalance in the brain, but they dont do it because of something that happened to them.  <br>
<br>
Also, I can tell you that being sexually abused as a child is NO REASON to sexually abuse another child when you are an adult.  Now, I have seen children who have been sexually abused and they will often act out their confusion through inappropriate sexual contact with others.  That I understand.  The child is confused and cannot make sense of what has happened to them.  But when an ADULT sexually abuses a child, and then uses the excuse of having been sexually abused as a child themselves, that is utter bullshit.  As an adult you understand what you are doing is wrong.  You have the option of speaking with someone about your issues.  As above, having been wronged does not give you the right to wrong others.<br>
<br>
Halo, you said we need to make a place where everyone isnt a victim.  I agree.  I think we need to realize that when someone hurts another person, the person being HURT is the victim, not the person doing the hurting.  I dont care if you were slapped around a lot as a child, or if you were picked on in school, or if you had pimples and were shunned for being ugly.  Those are NOT reasons to hurt other people!  You are an adult, you are fucking expected to treat others as they deserve to be treated.  This means if you start having feelings of aggression that you cant handle, get some help!  Once you start hurting others for the hurts you have been given, you cease to be the victim and become the victimizer.<br>
<br>
Justice is the administration of the law, revenge is taking vengeance for injuries or wrongs.  A person has the right to justice, but not revenge.  Meaning:  if you have been harmed, you are within your rights to seek reparations through the law, but NOT by acting on your own.<br>
<br>
To sum up... having been hurt in the past is not an excuse to hurt others in the present.  If you chose to hurt another person, that is your choice; but you had better be willing to accept the consequences.<br>
<br>
Stymp McStump<br>
