I don't like to throw out credintials to make everyone here think I know more then you, or that my opinions are more valid than yours, but I will this time so that you can see where I am coming from (not to say I am better than anyone.)  I have degrees in Criminology and Psychology, and my mother did her clinicals at the hospital Stymp mentions in his post, I think.  (No he and I have never met, or even talked outside of the msg boards).  As stated above, I am not trying to set myself up as better than anyone because I have studied so much in Crimnal Psych (I am actually working as an engineer and not in the field - too heart breaking for me.)<br>
<br>
However, I do agree that there are certain crimes that you can commit that are dire enough to loose your life, and I agree with Stymp that using the excuse of &quot;I am a victim so it wasn't my fault&quot; excuse is for the weak and cowardly.<br>
<br>
I now live in TX, and as all know we have a revolving door on the death chamber down in Huntsville.  I have no problem with the way we do things here.<br>
<br>
For the person that said we are playing God, I disagree.  We are judging the persons actions here on Earth and for those that we deem need it, we sent them to meet God for their final judgement.  Only God can judge the soul and punish it.  We can, however, prevent that soul from continuing down its present path.  (DAMMIT - You have me soundling like a preacher and I hate that!!!)<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp worth.<br>
<br>
PS Since I have yet to kill anyone, I am allowed to excercise my right to speak.  I also agree with who ever said, that when you are convicted of a capital crime, you loose all rights pertaining to life, liberty and pursuuit of hapiness (although I do feel that no one looses the right to due process)<br>
<br>
