<br>
Murder is &quot;the unlawful killing of a human being by another with malice aforethought, either express or implied.&quot;  Black's Law Dictionary 5th ed.<br>
<br>
Sorry Bri but you are wrong.  In no shape or form is the death penalty &quot;murder.&quot;  Not only is it legal but you lack the mens rea (malice aforethought) to assign to the jury/executioner.  <br>
<br>
The death penalty is simply the highest form of punishment the US society allows.  There have been some creative minds in this thread that think the death penalty is not the highest form of punishment and have come up with some different punishment.  Nevertheless, the general consensus of the US is that the death penalty is an appropriate punishment in limited circumstances (as decided by a cross-section of the US) and that other harsher forms of punishment should not be inflicted.<br>
<br>
